# Annotate It ‚úçÔ∏è

<!-- FULL_CODE_START
@RestController
@RequestMapping("/api/users")
public class UserController {
    // methods here
}
FULL_CODE_END -->

`@RestController` implies `@Controller` + `@ResponseBody` (returns data vs view).

# Simple Endpoint üëã

<!-- FULL_CODE_START
@GetMapping("/hello")
public String sayHello() {
    return "Hello World!";
}
FULL_CODE_END -->

Returns plain text 'Hello World!'.

# Dynamic URLs üÜî

Use `{id}` in the path and `@PathVariable` in the method.

<!-- FULL_CODE_START
@GetMapping("/{id}")
public User getUser(@PathVariable Long id) {
    return userService.findById(id);
}
FULL_CODE_END -->

# Query Strings üîç

Handle `/search?query=java`.

<!-- FULL_CODE_START
@GetMapping("/search")
public List<User> search(@RequestParam String query) {
    return userService.search(query);
}
FULL_CODE_END -->

# POST Payload üì¶

Receive JSON from client.

<!-- FULL_CODE_START
@PostMapping
public User createUser(@RequestBody User user) {
    return userService.save(user);
}
FULL_CODE_END -->

Spring automatically converts JSON -> Java Object.

# Full Control üéÆ

Return HTTP Status codes and headers.

<!-- FULL_CODE_START
@GetMapping("/{id}")
public ResponseEntity<User> get(@PathVariable Long id) {
    User user = userService.findById(id);
    if (user == null) return ResponseEntity.notFound().build();
    return ResponseEntity.ok(user);
}
FULL_CODE_END -->

# Safe Input üõ°Ô∏è

Use `@Valid` to trigger Bean Validation.

<!-- FULL_CODE_START
@PostMapping
public User create(@Valid @RequestBody User user) {
    // ...
}
FULL_CODE_END -->

# Global Handler üåç

`@ControllerAdvice` handles exceptions across all controllers.

<!-- FULL_CODE_START
@ControllerAdvice
public class GlobalExceptionHandler {
    @ExceptionHandler(UserNotFoundException.class)
    public ResponseEntity<String> handle(Exception e) {
        return ResponseEntity.status(404).body(e.getMessage());
    }
}
FULL_CODE_END -->
